! Mount point

The widget is injected into `document.body` at boot via the startup module `widgets/cascade-palette-startup.js`. Mount-point ID: `rimir-cascade-palette-mount`. To inspect: `document.getElementById("rimir-cascade-palette-mount")`.

! Console diagnostics

The widget only logs on error paths (no boot noise):

* `[cascade-palette] startup mount complete — widget in document.body` — startup module ran successfully (one-time at boot)
* `[cascade-palette] action invocation failed: ...` — `invokeViaNavigator()` threw (most likely a filter or wikitext error in `ca-actions` / `ca-next-scope` / `ca-next-default-action`)
* `[cascade-palette] ca-visibility-filter error on ...` — a root-entry's visibility filter threw; entry stays visible defensively
* `[cascade-palette] ca-template-applies error on ...` — a template's filter threw; template is excluded
* `[cascade-palette] template render error ...` — the template body wikitext failed to parse; the drawer shows the error message in place of the template
* `[cascade-palette] stack depth N exceeds soft warning M — possible cascade loop?` — the user has drilled past the soft-depth-warning threshold
